  <summary>4/7/1995--Introduced.
Public Pension Equity Restoration Act of 1995 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow deferred compensation to be included in governmental retirement plans. Makes inapplicable to governmental plans the rule which limits benefits to 100 percent of the average compensation for the highest three years. Removes excess benefit arrangements and survivor and disability benefits from limitations on governmental plans. Provides a mechanism to pay benefits above limitations to certain employees.</summary>
